@Johnny Depp I never thought in all my born days someone like you would ever respond to a comment of mine. I don't remember the name of the first movie but you played a widower with a young daughter. The daughter gets kidnapped and her kidnapper demands you kill a lady mayor or governor. You made friends with an elderly shoe shine man who believed your character. I've been a fan ever since. As to "fun place" well around here there's only the casino and in August the local city fair. Most of the things we used to do have been canceled. We had a jazz festival to honor Bix Beiderbecke. Don't know if it will be held this year thanks to the bug that must not be named. There was also a 5k run that a lot of Kenyan runners used to prep for the Olympics. A St. Patrick's Day parade, fireworks on the Fourth. A minor league baseball team, The River Bandits. 
You take care of yourself, after all, there's only one Johnny Depp 💖😍
